            <p class="font-semibold">Shadow Line</p>
            <p>Write one sentence starting, “A part of me is…” (jealous/angry/afraid). No judging, just naming.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="font-semibold">Solitude Slot</p>
            <p>Ten minutes, no phone. Sit, breathe, and ask: <em>What actually matters to me today?</em></p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="font-semibold">One Lamp Act</p>
            <p>Do one small meaningful thing (water the plant, call the friend, fix the hinge) with care.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="font-semibold">Perspective Ping</p>
            <p>When the crowd is loud, say: “I need time to think.” Buy yourself 24 hours.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="font-semibold">Connection Rep</p>
            <p>Send one message that says something real. Or listen, fully, for five minutes.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Closing -->
      <section class="mt-10 prose prose-invert max-w-none">
        <h2>Closing</h2>
        <p>Jung doesn’t offer an easy path—he offers a real one: face the shadow, honor your unique path, seek meaning in small faithful acts, and stand as a conscious individual amid the crowd. The world will stay noisy. But his compass points inward, to solid ground.</p>
        <p>The journey to become who you truly are is the privilege of a lifetime—difficult, costly, and worth everything.</p>
